.TH "kvm_vz_resize_guest_vtlb" 9 "kvm_vz_resize_guest_vtlb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_vz_resize_guest_vtlb \- Attempt to resize guest VTLB.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" kvm_vz_resize_guest_vtlb
.BI "(unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
Number of guest VTLB entries (0 < \fIsize\fP <= root VTLB entries).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Attempt to resize the guest VTLB by writing guest Config registers. This is
necessary for cores with a shared root/guest TLB to avoid overlap with wired
entries in the root VTLB.
.SH "RETURN"
The resulting guest VTLB size.
